The paper deals with information theory and specifically with the degrees of freedom (DoF) of a broadcast channel under channel uncertainty. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves mathematical proofs and analysis, which could fall under cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The concept of DoF is also relevant to multi-user systems, which could place the paper in categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its results on interference and X networks, which could place it in the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
